    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> I think a good heuristic for assessing misbehavior could be the count of the difficulty that a given signer has contributed during the current epoch.\r\n\r\nEdge case to consider is a signer that was voted in during the current epoch (and might be considered 'misbehaving' according to this metric).  \r\n\r\nI think instead we can measure a ratio of `difficulty that was contributed / difficulty that could have been contributed since the establishment of the signer (if it was voted in this epoch)`",
